stageCommonData.name: Barren Plaza
stageCommonData.description: A wide-open space in the middle of the slums, filled with haphazardly discarded garbage and vagrants with nowhere else to go. However, this place has also become a suitable den for enemies to hide.

stageCommonData.name: Abandoned High-rise
stageCommonData.description: This high-rise was abandoned after being destroyed by the flames of war, and was subsequently captured by the enemy. They now leverage the visibility it brings to defend their territory - we must recapture it.

stageCommonData.name: Area 59 Ruins
stageCommonData.description: This district within Chernobog was abandoned due to its small size and lack of strategic significance. It has since been occupied by wandering enemy forces, and we must recapture it to prevent enemies from slipping through our encirclement.

level_rune_01-01.runeDesc: This cooperation agreement supplies aid to Rhodes Island in the form of armaments, which can dramatically improve offensive capabilities. Though Rhodes Island will not be settling this operation independently, such a fact should not hamper the fulfillment of most tactical objectives.

This cooperation agreement will launch assaults to other areas, allowing Operators to attack key targets with greater efficiency. Though Rhodes Island will not be settling this operation independently, such a fact should not hamper the fulfillment of most tactical objectives.

This cooperation agreement will bolster combat supplies, provide better field medicine, and enhance protective conditions in battle. Though Rhodes Island will not be settling this operation independently, such a fact should not hamper the fulfillment of most tactical objectives.
Our objective in this operation is very specific, and any mistakes will cause the operation to fail.
